<section>
    <form action="/result" method="post" class="row">
        <div class="row"></div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col">
                <label class="form-label" for="searchTerm"><h4>Need a free image? Enter the thing you'd like to see (required):</h4></label>
                <input class="form-control" type="text" id="searchTerm" placeholder="Search Term" name="searchTerm">
            </div> 
            <div class="col"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="row"></div>
        <div class="p-3 mb-2 bg-light text-dark"> <b>Optional parameters</b>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col">
                    <label class="form-label" for="width">Specifiy width:</label>
                    <input class="form-control" type="number" id="width" placeholder="Width (px)" name="width">
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <label class="form-label" for="height"><b>OR</b> specify height:</label>
                    <input class="form-control" type="number" id="height" placeholder="Height (px)" name="height">
                </div>
            </div>
            <p></p>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col">Need to obscure this image? Select a level of pixelation from the dropdown menu:
                    <select class="form-select" aria-label="Default select example" name="pixelation">
                        <option value="0" selected>0% pixelated</option>
                        <option value="25">25% pixelated</option>
                        <option value="50">50% pixelated</option>
                        <option value="75">75% pixelated</option>
                        <option value="100">100% pixelated</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div class="col"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg col-2">Submit</button>
        </div>
    </form>    
</section>
<p></p>
<section>
    <h3>How it works</h3>
    <p>
        Given a search term, the Image Scraper gets “the single most appropriate thumbnail associated with [a Wikipedia] article”, in part by using 
        the PageImages property of MediaWiki’s API: https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:PageImages. Image pixelation is provided by Ian Ording’s 
        Image Transformer Microservice. The Image Scraper will then display the requested image and its attribution details for you to download. 
    </p>
    <p><b>Note: </b>This service will only return free images, such as those under the Creative Commons licence.</p>
